Objectives / Learning Outcome(s) / Major:
STUDENT LEARNING OUTCOMES (SLO'S)	
DISTINGUISH THE PURPOSES OF ACCOUNTING FOR BUSINESSES VERSUS GOVERNMENTAL OR NONPROFIT  ENTITIES;  
BE ABLE TO APPLY THE CONCEPTS OF GOVERNMENTAL AND NONPROFIT ACCOUNTING TO SOLVE  PROBLEMS FACING THESE ENTITIES;
BE ABLE TO DESCRIBE THE CURRENT PRACTICES OF GOVERNMENTAL AND NONPROFIT ACCOUNTING;
BE ABLE TO SUMMARIZE THE FUND ACCOUNTING CYCLE;
DEMONSTRATE COMPETENCY IN GOVERNMENT ACCOUNTING BY COMPLETING AN ANALYSIS OF A COMPREHENSIVE ANNUAL FINANCIAL REPORT;
BE ABLE TO APPLY CONCEPTS AND DEMONSTRATE COMPETENCY BY COMPLETING FINANCIAL RECORDS FOR A CITY UTILIZING PROPER JOURNAL ENTRIES;

